Hematologic (Table 63-7
) and serum biochemistry (Table 63-8
) values of nondomestic bovids may vary within and among subfamilies. Measurement of fibrinogen is generally more useful than a WBC count for assessing inflammation in bovids, and protein electrophoresis may be useful in monitoring chronic inflammation. Serum bile acids are a useful measure for monitoring the course of hepatic disease and its response to therapy.10
